commentTextItems.html: driven down the ground, Murali comes around, picks up the ball, throws the ball, a disillusioned Dravid wants the second. It is all over! Sri Lanka win by six runs!

commentPostTextItems.html: Sri Lanka win their second match in the tournament. India have nothing to show, they have lost both their matches.
It was always going to be difficult to score 222 for a win. The top order fell apart like a house of cards.

Amay Khurasiya making a comeback failed miserably. He doesn't really seem to be anywhere near international standar, walking all over the crease, a sitting duck for lbw and Perera was the lucky man to get him.
Yuvraj is completely lost as an opener. Laxman is not the man who played against Australia, his foot work is not worth a mention.
The wisdom ofsending in Harbhajan Singh as a pinch hitter defies all logic. He didn't know what to do in the middle, to block or to hit and scooped a tame catch.
Ganguly dropped himself down the order to save himself from the new ball and the faster bowlers. Make no mistake, this man Fernando is quick, the speed gun had him clockin in the 90's.
Ganguly stuck around to make a half century, but then he too wa a disillusioned man. 69 off 105 balls wasn't going to be big enough
Dravid remained unbeaten on 49 from 81 balls. Not being able to force the pace, not even a single boundary in his innings. This is a limited over match.
Sodhi was brimming with bravado but was undone by the magician, a sheer beauty which went through the gate. Muralitharan was a pure joy to watch.
He claimed the vital wickets of sodhi and Sehwag, when India looked like getting, clawing back into the match.
Murali's spell of 10-1-35-2 was sheer magic. he is the CricInfo's Top Performer of the Day!
India cannot be relying on Tendulkar alone, he is cooling his injured heel in Mumbai.
It is going to be an uphill task for the Indian team. Ganguly clearly a dejected man after the match. A lot of planning has to be done to pull this team out of the woods.
A happy and relieved Sanath Jayasuriya, two wins out of two, it can't get any better than this, the team-work was there to be seen.
Suresh Perera is the Man of the Match for his opening burst 6-0-26-2
Thats all we have for you from Premadasa Stadium, Colombo.
there has been too magic moments today. sodhi being bowled by Muralitharan and the big grin on umpire Peter Manuel's face as he gave out Khurasiya Lbw!
On that lighter note we will take leave. Kindly send in your opinions/copmments to comms@cricinfo.com
The next match is on the 25th Wednesday, It will feature New Zealand and Sri Lanka.
We will be with you with all the live action at 1000 Hrs local time, 0930 Hrs IST, 0400 GMT.
Good night and so long.
